Finance Minister Tito Mboweni during a media briefing after his first mid-term budget speech at Parliament on October 24, 2018. JOHANNESBURG - Pictures of Finance Minister Tito Mboweni at an ANC NEC meeting at Luthuli House in Johannesburg have caused a stir on social media. Mboweni, dressed in a black suit, was criticised for wearing what many people considered as 'dirty shoes.' READ: Tito Mboweni's beef stew receives mixed reviews Some people said what the minister deliberately wore the shoes as a publicity stunt. However, many other social media users defended the minister and said the shoes were probably comfortable.